{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:32:38.654937", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverall assessment\n- Network is in a critical failure state: no data-plane connectivity between hosts, even for same-subnet peers on the same leaf.\n- All Open vSwitch (OVS) devices (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are disconnected from the SDN controller and have no OpenFlow entries installed. With fail_mode set to secure, they drop all traffic, preventing ARP/forwarding.\n\nObserved symptoms\n- Intra-leaf L2/L3 failure:\n  - host_1_1 → host_1_2 ping: 100% loss; “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1.\n  - host_2_1 → host_2_2 ping: 100% loss; “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.5.\n- ARP resolution failing across hosts:\n  - ip neigh on hosts shows peers as FAILED (e.g., host_1_1: “10.0.0.2 FAILED”).\n- Hosts’ NICs are up with correct IP /24, but RX packet counters on all hosts are zero or near-zero, indicating nothing is received from the switches.\n\nControl-plane findings (OVS)\n- All switches are configured to use controller tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 with fail_mode: secure.\n- Controller connectivity status on all switches:\n  - is_connected: false\n  - status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF\n  - This shows the TCP connection reaches the target but is refused (no listener on 20.0.0.100:6633), indicating the controller process is not accepting connections rather than a management network reachability issue.\n- No OpenFlow rules installed:\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 returns empty flow tables (no entries).\n\nLocalization\n- Data-plane devices affected: leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 (all OVS instances).\n- Fault domain: SDN control plane endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633 (controller service). The management network path is likely intact (connection is refused, not timed out), so the issue is localized to the controller host/service itself rather than the OVS devices or management network links.\n\nRoot cause\n- The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100:6633 is not listening/accepting TCP connections (connection refused). Because all OVS switches are in fail_mode secure and have no flows, they drop all traffic. This prevents ARP and L2/L3 forwarding, causing complete loss of host-to-host connectivity.\n\nImpact scope\n- Complete outage for all hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 across both leaves and the spine. No ARP responses; no intra- or inter-leaf communication.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9558, "output_tokens": 1758, "total_tokens": 11316, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9216}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1152}}}
